Pretoria - President Jacob Zuma has wished South African gospel music star, Lundi Tyamara, a speedy recovery.According to media reports, Tyamara has been admitted to a Johannesburg hospital for some weeks as he battles ill health.Tyamara, one of South Africa's premier gospel artists and a multi-award winner, has been hospitalised since December last year. President Zuma has urged South Africans to keep Tyamara and his family in their thoughts and prayers. SAnews.gov.zaPretoria - Condolences are pouring in for the late gospel singer Lundi Tyamara who passed away in the early hours of this morning.Pretoria - Popular gospel singer Lundi Tyamara has passed away, his management announced on Friday.